# Airtable Automation Script Standard

Full doc: `airtable/automations/AUTOMATION_SCRIPT_STANDARD.md`

When creating or editing `airtable/automations/**/*.js`, follow that standard and existing production patterns (**066 v3.1 V2 reference**, 114, 034, 005, 063, 101, 072, 074).

## File and metadata

- Name: `{number}-{kebab-case}.js` in `shooting-challenge/`
- GitHub header at top (GitHub only); production docblock after it
- Docblock: Version, Date Written (preserve earliest), Last Updated (today on logic edits)
- Docblock sections: PURPOSE, IMPORTANT DESIGN RULES, INPUT, OUTPUTS, TRIGGER, AUTOMATION NAME, FOLDER; add RECOMMENDED/OPTIONAL/DO NOT USE triggers, "This is not…", FIELD RENAME FIX when relevant
- `// @ts-nocheck` after docblock
- **`SCRIPT`** metadata block: `scriptName`, `version`, `versionDate`, `originalWrittenDate`, `lastUpdated`, `folder`, `automationName` — must match docblock
- **`CONFIG`** for tables, fields, statuses, actions, and business configuration only (no script identity)
- V2 rewrites: one section changes → rewrite full section; multiple sections → rewrite full script (no isolated patches unless emergency hotfix)

## Structure

- **Wrap in `async function main()`** — new scripts and substantive edits only; legacy 009/013/020/021/057/058/063/072/074/075/111/112 exempt until touched
- End with `try { await main(); } catch` (114) or `await main()` with catch inside main (034)
- Numbered `SECTION N:` blocks for scripts over ~150 lines
- **`debugStep`** — update and `setOutputSafe("debugStep", ...)` before each major step

## Inputs / outputs

- `input.config()`; validate `recordId` non-empty and `startsWith("rec")`
- **Required outputs:** `statusOut` (success|skipped|error), `errorOut`, `debugStep`
- **`actionOut`** — created, updated, skipped_*, error (document in docblock)
- **Skip** = set skipped outputs + return; **Error** = set outputs + throw
- `setOutputSafe` for all `output.set`; final `console.log(JSON.stringify({ automation, version, ... }))`

## Schema and fields

- Validate schema early: requireField, requireFieldType, requireWritableField, requireSingleSelectOption
- fieldCache + getFieldSafe on larger scripts; unloadData() after large selectRecordsAsync
- Reads: getRaw, getText, getNumber (display fallback), getCheckbox/getBooleanish, getLinkedIds
- Writes: addIfWritable, updateRecordSafe, updateRecordBestEffort; skip if value unchanged
- Single-select (new edits): validate option, write `{ id: match.id }` (114 pattern)
- Never write formula, rollup, lookup, count, or other computed fields

## Dates

- Weeks Start/End Date: dateTime, America/Denver — use 005/034 toDateKeyFromText + toDateKeyFromDateObject; not raw `new Date("M/D/YYYY")` alone

## Domain rules

- **XP:** Source Key in docblock; one source record → one XP Event; guard against stealing; Reason Public + Reason Debug; recheck before create (114)
- **Email/Make:** build package then send; webhook from input; fetch with error body; don't clear send trigger on webhook failure (074)
- **Copy/link:** skip if already matches; "This is not…" scope in docblock (063, 111)
- **Weekly summary:** don't write rollup/formula weekly totals; 034 chain uses Week Start Date order
- **General:** idempotent, append-only XP Events, skip vs error distinction

## Deploy

GitHub first → paste docblock through end into Airtable (skip GitHub header) → CHANGELOG if production-impacting

Do not change script logic when only updating headers unless user asked for a fix.
